## Key Optimizations Implemented

1.  **POD & Anonymous Union Event System**: Refactored the core [Event](file:///c:/Users/BIT/hft_system/core/events.hpp#68-85) union to be a pure Plain Old Data (POD) structure, enabling high-performance memory copies and cache-friendly access.
2.  **Busy-Polling Event Loop**: Eliminated OS interrupt latency by using a busy-polling loop for the primary event processor.
3.  **Thread Affinity & Core Pinning**: Assigned critical feed and processing threads to dedicated physical CPU cores to prevent context-switch overhead.
4.  **Hardware-Aware Data Layout**: Aligned the core [Event](file:///c:/Users/BIT/hft_system/core/events.hpp#68-85) structure to the 64-byte CPU cache line to prevent false sharing and optimize prefetching.

